  <prompt>
    Create the new ADR-033 (Communication Architecture) codifying the canonical client-side Communication pattern that R3 implements. This ADR is the binding pre-write checkpoint for every subsequent R3 wave — without it landed first, the rest of the project lacks an authoritative anchor.

    The ADR must (a) confirm the canonical engine + wrappers + Code Page + typed wrapper structure, (b) capture the boundaries (what's in-scope vs out-of-scope per `sprk_communication` Code Page + `CommunicationType=Email` only), (c) reference ADR-024 (polymorphic resolver), ADR-028 (auth v2), ADR-026 (full-page custom page), and ADR-007 (SPE), and (d) be cross-referenced from `CLAUDE.md` §16 and `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` so the agent loads it on Communication-touching tasks.

    Re-verify ADR-033 is still the next free slot before creating (pre-flight confirmed it was free as of 2026-06-05 — `.claude/adr/ADR-032-*.md` is the highest existing). If a parallel project has claimed 033 in the interim, use the next free number and update all subsequent task references.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke platform architect. Authoritative on Communication architecture (R1 + R2 + R3 history). Familiar with the project's ADR conventions (concise `.claude/adr/` form, ~100–150 lines, MUST/MUST-NOT structure).
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new ADR file at `.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md` (concise form, ~100–150 lines) that codifies the canonical Communication architecture and is cross-referenced from `CLAUDE.md` §16 + `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`. ADR passes `/adr-check` against `spec.md`. No regressions in existing ADR loading.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      R1 built early email integration. R2 built the server-side Communication Service. R3 (this project) is the client-side consolidation — replaces 6 ad-hoc send-email implementations with one canonical engine + 3 wrappers + 1 Code Page + 1 typed BFF wrapper. ADR-033 codifies this so future surfaces don't re-fragment.

      The ADR is the FIRST artifact of R3 because every subsequent wave's code review and `/adr-check` cite it. Writing code first and ADR later would invert the discipline this project is designed to enforce.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/INDEX.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/INDEX.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-024">Server-side `IncomingAssociationResolver` unchanged; ADR-033 explicitly cites this boundary</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Code Page architecture follows Full-Page Custom Page standard</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">`@spaarke/auth` v2 is the only auth bootstrap; shared lib injects `authenticatedFetch`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">SPE archival uses existing facade; no client reaches SPE directly</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Communication services register via `CommunicationModule` only</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ADR-033 must be cross-referenced from `CLAUDE.md` §16 pointer table</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">ADR-033 must be cross-referenced from `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` ("Communication as sensitive surface" addition planned in Wave 6 task 087)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Concise ADR form per `.claude/adr/` conventions — NOT the full-history form in `docs/adr/`</constraint>
  </constraints>

